Daybreak AutoResearch is an agent-agnostic autonomous research protocol
packaged here as a Codex-compatible skill.

This project is an adapted and extended version of the open-sourced
Deli AutoResearch / Deli_AutoResearch framework originally created by
Deli Chen (DeepSeek).

Original references:
- https://x.com/victor207755822
- https://victorchen96.github.io/auto_research/framework.html

The Daybreak adaptation preserves the reliability spine of Deli AutoResearch
and adds STORM-style multi-perspective discovery, retrieval grounding, source
and claim ledgers, gap / contradiction / hypothesis tracking, a persistent
backbone synthesis layer, sufficiency-based completion, and the Discovery Tail
Pass.

The STORM-style discovery layer is inspired by Stanford OVAL's STORM project:
- https://storm-project.stanford.edu/research/storm/
- https://github.com/stanford-oval/storm
- https://arxiv.org/abs/2402.14207

This repository is not affiliated with Deli Chen, DeepSeek, Stanford OVAL, or
the STORM authors. Names and links are used only for attribution and lineage.

At packaging time, the upstream Deli AutoResearch skill was publicly announced
as open source, but no explicit upstream license type was located in the
framework page or visible repository paths. If an upstream license is later
published, this repository should be reviewed for compatibility.
